From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Mesa Contributor <contributor@example.com>
Date: Fri, 12 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] freedreno: add Adreno 7xx and 8xx GPU entries

Add support for Adreno 7xx series (710, 720, 722) and 8xx series (810, 829,
830, 840, X2-85) GPUs to freedreno_devices.py.

7xx Support:
Magic register values were derived from real blob command streams captured
as .rd traces and decoded with cffdump.

Chip IDs (7xx):
  FD710: 0x07010000 / wildcard 0xffff07010000
  FD720: 0x43020000 / wildcard 0xffff43020000
  FD722: 0x43020100 / wildcard 0xffff43020100

GMEM sizes (from KGSL_PROP_DEVICE_INFO, 7xx):
  FD710: 0x80000  (512 KiB)
  FD720: 0x100000 (1 MiB)
  FD722: 0x100000 (1 MiB)

All 7xx use CHIP.A7XX with the a7xx_base + a7xx_gen1 feature sets,
3 CCUs, 32 VSC pipes, 32 KiB shared memory, wave_granularity=2, and
fibers_per_sp = 128*2*16.

8xx Support:
Includes Adreno 810 (1 CCU), 830 (6 CCUs), 829 (4 CCUs), 840 (6 CCUs),
and X2-85 (8 CCUs). All 8xx devices use CHIP.A8XX with base features
and kernel-managed register programming.

Entries are inserted immediately before the FD725 block.

Signed-off-by: Mesa Contributor <contributor@example.com>
